==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sooterkin
<hw>Soot"er*kin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. Prov. G.
<ets>suttern</ets> to boil gently.]</ety> <def>A kind of false birth,
fabled to be produced by Dutch women from sitting over their stoves;
also, an abortion, in a figurative sense; an abortive scheme.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Fruits of dull heat, and <qex>sooterkins</qex> of wit.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sooth</ent>⟦br⟧
